  },

  "faq": {
    "heading": "Frequently Asked Questions",
    "q1": "Can I use mPay Wallet on multiple devices?",
    "a1": "Yes, you can sign in to your mPay account on multiple devices. However, for security reasons, <b>only one device can be active at a time</b>. Signing in on a new device will automatically sign you out of the previous one.",
    "q2": "What if I don't receive the OTP code?",
    "a2": "If you don't receive the OTP within 60 seconds, tap the \"Resend Code\" button. Make sure your phone has signal reception and SMS is not blocked. If the issue persists, try the \"Call Me\" option for voice verification. Check our Troubleshooting guide for more solutions.",
    "q3": "Is there a minimum deposit to start using the wallet?",
    "a3": "No, there is no minimum deposit required. You can create your account and explore the app without adding any funds. When you're ready to make a payment, you can fund your wallet with any amount. Check Wallet Management for funding options and limits.",
    "q4": "Can I change my phone number after registration?",
    "a4": "Yes, you can update your phone number from the Settings page. You'll need to verify your identity and the new phone number via OTP. The old number will be unlinked after successful verification. For security, there's a 24-hour cooling period before certain features are re-enabled after a number change.",
    "q5": "What should I do if the app crashes during setup?",
    "a5": "If the app crashes during setup, simply reopen it. Your progress is saved automatically at each step. If the problem persists, try clearing the app cache (Android) or reinstalling the app (iOS). Make sure you have the latest version installed. Visit our Troubleshooting page for more help.",
    "q6": "Is my personal data secure during registration?",
    "a6": "Absolutely. All data transmitted during registration is encrypted using industry-standard TLS 1.3. Your personal information is stored securely and never shared with third parties without your consent. Read our Privacy Policy for complete details on how we handle your data."
  },

